{"lemma":"صَوْمَعَةٍ","slug":"صَوْمَعَةٍ","root":"ص.م.ع","root_slug":"ص-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24927"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tower, minaret"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a monk’s cell or a hermit’s hut; monastic cell, hermitage","examples":[{"text":"وَلَوْلَا دَفْعُ ٱللهِ ٱلنَّاسَ بَعْضَهُمْ بِبَعْضٍ لَّهُدِّمَتْ صَوَامِعُ وَبِيَعٌ وَّصَلَوَاتٌ وَّمَسٰجِدُ يُذْكَرُ فِيهَا ٱسْمُ ٱللهِ كَثِيرًا","english":"And were it not that God checks some people by others there in fact would have been demolished monastic cells and churches, and synagogues and mosques wherein the name of God is oft-mentioned."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cellar, den; silo"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From an unknown Old South Arabian word, from which also Ge'ez ጾማዕት (ṣomaʿt)."},"ipa":["/sˤaw.ma.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24927","headword_ar":"صَوْمَعَةٌ","root":"SmE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Christian's cell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, KL,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for retirement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seclusion, having a high and slender head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cell of a recluse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a monk's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAr","text_ar":"مَنَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which, as here used, means likewise a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber, of the kind described above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomaEap","text_ar":"صَوْمَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Christians is thus called because it is slender in the head; (S, O, K;) or because contracted; (Msb;) or, as As says, from the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSomaEu","text_ar":"اَصْمَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning [that it is] pointed at the extremity, [or top,] and contracted: (TA:) and it is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomaEN","text_ar":"صَوْمَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAmiEu","text_ar":"صَوَامِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miy^o*anapN","text_ar":"مِيْذَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Lh, M and K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*n","text_ar":"اذن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, part of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mess of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variyd","text_ar":"ثَرِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled bread moistened with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body thereof: a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrydp","text_ar":"ثريدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mess of crumbled bread with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said to be thus called, when it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made pointed in its head, and made even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buronus","text_ar":"بُرْنُس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment with a pointed hood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) Aboo- 'Alee says, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAmiEu","text_ar":"صَوَامِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAnis","text_ar":"بَرَانِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) without mentioning a sing. thereof. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eagle"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus termed, because always upon the highest place to which it can ascend. (O, * K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","KL","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}